The Kensington Woods Schools Board of Education is now recruiting new members. Membership on the volunteer Board requires attending monthly meetings and guiding the running and growth of Kensington Woods Schools.

Board members are encouraged to be active members of the Livingston County community and have a passion for education and Kensington Woods Schools.

Please share with anyone you feel may be a good fit for the Board. Those interested can contact Board President C. J. Phillips at cjphillips5@outlook.com.

All classes are designed and taught by KWoods teachers, providing a quality learning experience for all.

Interested in learning more? Call 517-545-0828 or email info@kwoods.org.

shared_text:
Howell Melon Festival
August 6 at 8:00 PM ¬∑

The time has come to reveal which famous Howell resident is behind the Kensington Woods Schools Kenny the Bear mask. If you guessed Richard Lim of Richard Lim Photography, you're correct!

Lim has been a prominent Howell figure for years. In addition to running his photography business, Richard Lim Photography, he is a board member for the Howell DDA and the Howell Area Chamber of Commerce, serves on the Michigan Challenge Ballonfest Committee, and was even the Grand Marshall at last year's Fantasy of Lights Parade!

In addition, Richard is a volunteer extraordinaire and has volunteered his time and talents to many local groups including The Howell Melon Festival, the Community Theatre of Howell, Howell High School, and many, many more!

Thank you to Richard for participating in this year's Mascot Challenge and thank you to all who played along with us on facebook. Finally we'd like to once again we'd like to thank our friends at Howell Family Dentist for helping us put on this contest for the community! #HowellGrown #MelonFest2020

Take some time this summer to read, relax and connect in our Summer Book Club!

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

The value of reading cannot be stressed enough! Reading for pleasure is linked to success in school. An hour of sustained, recreational reading each day is encouraged during the summer. This year, we offer suggestions of books that are enjoyable and well-written. While we strongly encourage a regular reading schedule, this summer we will not be requiring students to read books from our list. Instead, we will offer extra credit in English to students who read regularly and contribute to our online summer book club. Start next year off with a boost!

Find out more info here: https://buff.ly/3eKo7xN

Google Classroom Codes:
Summer Book Club 2020‚ÄîMiddle School: apbl34r
Summer Book Club‚ÄîHigh School: 52tqvrb

The Summer Fitness Challenge has started but it‚Äôs not too late to get involved!

‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî‚Äî

All KWoods students and staff members are invited to participate in the KWoods 2020 Summer Fitness Challenge. A fitness challenge is a great time to explore activities that will get you moving and improve your well-being.

Participants will complete activities on their own but will have the opportunity to connect with each other in Google Classroom to share resources and to motivate one another.

All participants who finish the challenge will receive a KWoods Summer Fitness Challenge T-Shirt!

Goals
+ Complete 20 hours of fitness activities during the month of July
+ Complete 20 hours of fitness activities during the month of August

Steps
+ Join ‚ÄúKWoods 2020 Summer Fitness Challenge‚Äù on Google Classroom
Classroom code: 6cfqlde
+Record your fitness activities in the ‚ÄúFitness Record‚Äù located on Google Classroom
+ Share photos of some of your experiences
+ Have fun!

Did you know you can help earn KWoods money when you shop via Amazon? To date, KWoods families have earned the school over $700 just by making purchases they already planned on making! And now it's even easier!

AmazonSmile customers can now support Kensington Woods Parent Organization in the Amazon shopping app on iOS and Android mobile phones! Simply follow these instructions to turn on AmazonSmile and start generating donations.
1. Open the Amazon Shopping app on your device
2. Go into the main menu of the Amazon Shopping app and tap into 'Settings'
3. Tap 'AmazonSmile' and follow the on-screen instructions to complete the process

post_text:
A few weeks ago, Sophomore Hannah Montgomery participated in a Masterclass for singing with Broadway star Raquel Suarez Groen.

She says, "Over the course of two weeks, I participated in an online masterclass about building confidence in singing. I worked with Broadway star, Raquel Suarez Groen who plays Carlotta Giudicelli in The Phantom of the Opera, as well as a psychotherapist to help calm nerves and performance anxiety. One of the best things about it was that everyone involved were from different backgrounds, different parts of the world, and all ages. It was super inspiring!"

Great work Hannah! #kwoodsdifference

Livingston Career and College Access Network
May 19 at 11:31 AM ¬∑

Looking for something fun and safe for your daughter to do this summer? Check out mcwt.org for their new Summer Virtual Learning series that will begin early to mid-July and continue over a 6-week period with multiple sessions repeating over this time. The Summer Learning Program will consist of the following:

Week long camps with 2-3 hours per day engagement for Middle School and High School girls
Weekly Meet-Up 1 hour sessions open to all middle and high school girls, highlighting insights, best practices, stories from our amazing MCWT women and scholars too
The Summer Learning Program will be free of charge this summer and hoping to expand our impact to more girls throughout Michigan! Great way to give your child some technology career experiences from the safety of your home!

Details will be posted the week of June 1!

Week long camps with 2-3 hours per day engagement for Middle School and High School girls
Weekly Meet-Up 1 hour sessions open to all middle and high school girls, highlighting insights, best practices, stories from our amazing MCWT women and scholars too
The Summer Learning Program will be free of charge this summer and hoping to expand our impact to more girls throughout Michigan! Great way to give your child some technology career experiences from the safety of your home!

Details will be posted the week of June 1!

post_text:
We would like to congratulate Senior Alysia Gordon, whose work was selected for the Huron Valley Council for the Arts Climate Change show!

The exhibit will be hosted online and they are also hosting a virtual opening this Friday from 1-3pm, open to all! Consider registering to attend (info below!)

The work and videos from the artist (including Alysia) will be available to view on the Huron Valley Council for the Arts website starting on Friday. www.huronvalleyarts.org

The Zoom virtual opening on April 17, 2020 1:00pm-3:00pm. This zoom event will feature three artists (Joslyn Ho, Jim Williams and Dawn Smith). Each artist will talk about their studio practice and then give a mini art lesson that is appropriate for children along with a 5 min Q&A at the end.

You must pre-register for the opening. Once you register a code will be emailed to you to enter the event. https://buff.ly/2K9lCaM

post_text:
On Friday, April 3, Mr. Muennix will be in the building to check out equipment like Chromebooks, calculators and musical instruments in preparation of us beginning a more structured distance learning environment on Monday, April 6 when we return from Spring Break.

To aid in social distancing and keep a safe environment for all, there will only be one family allowed in the building at a time. Please sign up for a pickup time on the calendar below.
https://calendly.com/marmue/chromebook-calculator-checkout?month=2020-04

Also, please look for a more detailed email about our transition to distance learning in your email boxes later in the day tomorrow or early Friday morning.

We hope you are saying safe and well.
